{"ts":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z","author":"codex-root","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/body","value":"## Problem\n\nThe maintained Monica 4.x route inventory is already fully mapped, but live read-only research against the configured self-hosted instance returns HTTP 500 with `Failed to load trust proxies from Cloudflare server.` The CLI currently reduces this Monica-originated infrastructure failure to generic retry advice, so humans and agents cannot distinguish an instance configuration/dependency problem from a transient API failure.\n\n## Research basis\n\n- The checked-in 35-resource, 172-endpoint snapshot matches `monicahq/monica` branch `4.x` commit `32028ce3ce79cef38df5d27a297e5b20680f0065`.\n- The error originates in `monicahq/laravel-cloudflare` when Monica cannot fetch Cloudflare IPv4/IPv6 proxy ranges.\n- The configured instance is kept in global private settings with read-only mode enabled; no production records may be mutated.\n\n## Delivery scope\n\nAdd a typed, reusable server-diagnostic classifier; expose stable diagnostic codes and operator actions in connection doctor and capability reports; retain the original safe error message; document the diagnostic contract and self-hosted remediation; validate all output schemas, help, unit, coverage, source-quality, and actual read-only CLI paths.\n\n## Non-goals\n\nDo not modify Monica records, change the Monica server, expose credentials, or invent route families beyond the maintained 4.x source."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"monica-server-diagnostics"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Classify Monica server infrastructure failures with actionable diagnostics"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Turn known Monica-originated infrastructure failures into typed, agent-actionable diagnostics without masking the underlying API error."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":0},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","api-research","diagnostics","read-only","self-hosted"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/deadline","value":"2026-07-29T04:43:28.254Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/assignee","value":"codex-root"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"codex-root"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":180},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"Known Cloudflare trust-proxy loader failures expose a stable diagnostic code, cause, operator action, and authoritative source link in structured connection and capability output; unknown server failures retain generic retry guidance; all schemas and documentation match runtime output; full release gates and actual read-only CLI validation pass without changing Monica data"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/definition_of_ready","value":"Upstream 4.x routes and local all-status tracker inventory reviewed; duplicate search clean; private settings confirmed mode 0600 and read-only."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/goal","value":"Make monica-cli dependable and agent-ready on heterogeneous self-hosted Monica installations."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/objective","value":"Convert opaque instance-side HTTP 500 failures into deterministic remediation guidance."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/value","value":"Agents can stop futile retries and hand operators the correct self-hosted fix path."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/impact","value":"Faster incident diagnosis with no credential or CRM data exposure."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/outcome","value":"Connection doctor and capability reports identify the Cloudflare proxy loader failure consistently."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/why_now","value":"The configured production instance currently exhibits this exact failure and blocks all read-only API research."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"monica-api-4x-parity"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/reviewer","value":"github-bots"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/reporter","value":"codex-root"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/severity","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/environment","value":"Self-hosted Monica 4.x at private LAN URL; CLI 2026.7.21-2; readOnlyMode=true"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/repro_steps","value":"Run monica --json config test or monica --json info capabilities --refresh; observe HTTP 500 trust-proxy loader message."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/expected_result","value":"CLI returns a stable, structured diagnostic with operator remediation and retains the original API error."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/actual_result","value":"CLI reports only a generic transient API error and suggests retrying."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/affected_version","value":"2026.7.21-2"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/component","value":"configuration and capability diagnostics"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/regression","value":false},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/customer_impact","value":"All API command families appear generically unavailable, preventing agents from selecting a correct remediation."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"monica-api-4x-parity-plan","kind":"discovered_from","created_at":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z"},{"id":"monica-config-output-secret-sink","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z"},{"id":"monica-platform","kind":"blocked_by","created_at":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z"},{"id":"monica-settings-permissions","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z"}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Live read-only reproduction confirmed the failure across config test and all 34 capability probes; no Monica records were modified."}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Implementation must centralize message classification so config doctor, capability inventory, and future surfaces do not drift."}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-22T04:43:28.254Z","author":"codex-root","text":"Upstream API parity can be complete while instance operability remains blocked; route coverage and server health must remain separate dimensions."}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/files","value":[{"path":"src/commands/config-doctor.ts","scope":"project","note":"structured connection diagnosis"},{"path":"src/commands/info-capabilities.ts","scope":"project","note":"capability remediation guidance"}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tests","value":[{"command":"bun run test:coverage","scope":"project","timeout_seconds":240}]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/docs","value":[{"path":"docs/INSTANCE-COMPATIBILITY.md","scope":"project","note":"self-hosted operator remediation"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"05bf5d3906b44867220a9821d90ebeb2110f6b898955480f801197370b2fa985","message":"Track live Monica server diagnostic enhancement"}
